title: 雪でも使える GITZO オーシャントラベラー三脚 GK1581OT
tags: ['GITZO', 'オーシャントラベラー', '三脚キット', 'GK1581OT', '防塵三脚', '防滴三脚', 'オーシャンロック', 'チタニウムトラベラー', '秋葉仁', '秋葉原', '海岸での三脚', '軽い三脚', '手軽三脚']
description:
どんな状況でも使用可能なGITZO オーシャントラベラー三脚 GK1581OTですが、これが実に使いやすいのです。
今日みたいに雪が降っている状況でも気にする事なく使う事が出来ます。
とても軽く、移動もスムーズで夏は海岸での使用も可能です。
秋葉仁が持ち出す三脚の中で登板が多いのですが・・・
寒い！
さすがに寒かったです！

【商品紹介】
ジッツオ初のステンレススチールを基幹部品に採用した三脚であるだけでなく、世界で初めて過酷な天候や環境に挑戦するために開発された三脚。90周年限定モデルとして発売された「チタニウムトラベラー」の設計と製造技術を継承。
オーシャントラベラーは、塩水、砂、泥、湿気といった困難な環境での使用のために新たに開発された機能と、トラベラーシリーズならではのコンパクト性を組み合わせています。この独自の組み合わせにより、オーシャントラベラーはこのような環境で撮影を行うフォトグラファーにとって理想の携帯アイテムです。
Gロックの完成形とも言える革新的な「オーシャンロック」。ロック両端の特殊なインサートにより、チューブやロック機構内への水や砂の浸入を最小限に食い止めます。チューブ内に浸入した僅かな水も、ステンレス製の脚上端部に備えられた特殊なじょうご状の穴から流し出すことが可能。

title: Sonoma Valley Wine Tasting Tour - Gloria Ferrer Winery
description:
On February 24, 2008 we went on an interesting excursion out of San Francisco: an ecologically friendly bio-diesel powered van from Incredible Adventures whisked us off to the outlying areas north of San Francisco. After our first stop at Muir Woods to admire the giant redwoods we embarked on our tour to wine country. Through the rain we drove north into the Sonoma Valley, one of the two world-famous wine-making areas north of San Francisco. The other, even more famous wine-making area, is the adjacent Napa Valley.

The Sonoma Valley is actually the birthplace of the Californian wine industry and encompasses 13,000 acres of parkland. Before lunch we stopped at two wineries, Roche and Homewood Wineries, where we got to taste a whole variety of red and white wines and even some local olives and olive oils. For lunch we stopped off on the main square of Sonoma where my friend and I grabbed a tasty lunch at the Basque Café.

After lunch we headed into the Castle Winery just off Sonoma's main square that surprised us with a sweet sherry and a delicious sherry chocolate sauce. Our last stop on this excursion were the Gloria Ferrer Caves and Vineyards which produce world-class award-winning sparkling wines as well as Chardonnay and Pinot Noir. The Ferrer family's involvement with sparkling wine goes back several centuries in Catalonia, Spain, and their most famous product is Freixenet, a world famous sparkling wine made according to the méthode champenoise.

Properly educated about wine and definitely in a much lighter mood after all these tastings, we started heading back to the city. The atmosphere in the van was downright giggly. Michelle stopped at a lookout point overlooking the northern terminus of the bridge which provided us with an excellent view, despite the cold winds and the grey and rainy skies.

At the end of our excursion, we got conveniently dropped off on the doorsteps of our hotel, the Queen Anne, and after recovering for a bit, we took the 22 bus and went for a nice dinner to Tangerine SF, a beautiful restaurant that features Pan Asian cuisine, located in the SoMa district of San Francisco. After a great filling dinner and a long conversation with the owners Steve and Sean we walked all the way back to our hotel on Fillmore Street, a pleasant 45 minute walk through beautiful Victorian neighbourhoods.

¿Qué pasaría si Lyon terminase por unirse a ti en el historia y derrotase al demonio que intentó poseerlo? Aquí está la batalla entre Lyon (versión jefe final pero con todas sus estadísticas maxeadas) y el Rey Demonio, con sus estadísticas y sus magias originales. Lyon además de poseer Naglfar, la magia que tiene al final del juego y con la que viene como personaje secreto, tiene tres elixires que son necesarios ya que ni un Lyon maxeado puede vencer solo al Rey Demonio. No tuve otra elección que usar dos de ellos.

El juego está modificado mediante un programa llamado Nightmare. Con él pueden modificarse los tres juegos de Game Boy Advance: Sword of Seals, Blazing Sword y Sacred Stones.

description:
Dancer: Ebony
Choreography: Ebony
Music: "Beauty Beats" by Beats Antique from Collide
Performance: 7th Annual Under a Desert Moon, May 3rd 2009

Sahara Dance, Washington DC's Center for Middle Eastern Dance, is a boutique dance studio dedicated to celebrating the joy and beauty of belly dance. 

Seeking to create a community for belly dancers and to elevate belly dance as a performance art, Sahara Dance produces annual theater productions highlighting both traditional and experimental belly dance. Founded in 2004, Sahara Dance offers over 50 weekly belly dance classes at 7 locations in DC, MD and VA. 

The studio is home to 16 faculty members, five resident performance companies, and over 600 belly dancers.  http://saharadance.com

En plus, je suis bilingue alors pourquoi pas chanter ma chanson dans les deux langues? C'est pas traduit mot pour mot (il faut que ca rime!) mais c'est plus ou moins semblable. J'espère que vous l'aimer! GO HABS GO!

description:
Swiper swipes the Elements in S2 Episode 1. The music has been replaced with the Star Wars Episode I OST, composed by John Williams and performed by the London Symphony Orchestra.

Part of my MLP Star Wars OST project, an experimental series of videos featuring scenes from MLP accompanied by the Star Wars OST. The purpose of this project is to show Hasbro what MLP might be like if William Anderson (the composer of the fantastic MLP OST) were given a full orchestra or higher-quality samples to work with; it's also just for fun!

title: WW2 Sexton Self Propelled Gun Firing at Explosion! Gosport, UK
tags: ['Gun', 'Sexton', 'Explosion! Museum Of Naval Firepower (Building)', 'World War II (Event)', 'Gosport', 'Self-propelled Gun', 'WW2', 'Reenactment', 'Firing', 'Artillery']
description:
A video of a Sexton self-propelled artillery vehicle moving into position and then firing five rounds as part of the 'Spirit of the 40s' event being held at the Explosion! Museum of Naval Firepower (Priddy's Hard - former Royal Naval Armaments Depot in Gosport, UK). Another video from this event can be found at http://youtu.be/AqYAy1A9Ejs.

Britain asked Canada to develop a vehicle for its 25 pounder gun during World War 2 and over 2,150 Sextons were built by the Montreal Locomotive Works. Of these, only around 5 examples remain in the UK, and of them this is the only example that is still allowed to fire its 25 pounder field gun. This example was built in late 1943 / early 1944.

title: Johnny Hallyday - Gabrielle (Live at Montreux 1988)
description:
Johnny Hallyday is a French icon and superstar. With a career going back into the fifties he remains the best selling artist of all time in the French speaking world as well as enjoying a successful acting career. Inspired by Elvis Presley and the pioneers of American rock 'n' roll he managed to take their energy and sense of rebellion and create something distinctively French. He was an immediate success and has remained so to this day. This concert from Montreux in 1988 captures his electric live show in a far more intimate venue than the vast arenas he usually performs in.

title: WRC craziest moments
description:
DVD Available here : http://bit.ly/TsGYv3

In the World Rally Championship anything can happen - and usually does! Get ready to experience the most spectacular, shocking and hilarious incidents from almost two decades of high speed drama.

Exceptional action footage, including plenty from inside the cars, charts the Craziest Moments from the WRC. Legends including Colin McRae, Sebastien Loeb, Richard Burns, Tommi Makinen, Marcus Gronholm, Carlos Sainz, Petter Solberg and many more treat us to the thrills and spills which make rallying one of the most spectacular sports on Earth.

You'll see the best drivers coping with ever-changing weather, heart-breaking retirements and getting too close for comfort with the wildlife - including some naked Swedes! There's also scorching fires, flaring tempers, wacky fans and the madcap antics of the charismatic and always-entertaining Gigi Galli.

WRC's Craziest Moments also gives you the chance to experience the highs and lows of life as a co-driver, from the elation of victory to the bone-shattering crash landings - plus the story of the stray metal pole which left its mark on Timo Rautiainen's posterior!

Discover what the crews do to keep the cars on the road, including making use of swimming pools, shoe laces and turning rocks into tools, and share the heart-break of coming within metres of World Championship success only to lose out with the end in sight.

Alongside the mud-spitting, car-wrecking, spine-jarring action we hear the full stories behind these craziest moments from the drivers, co-drivers including Phil Mills, Robert Reid, Nicky Grist, Daniel Elena and Luis Moya, plus team bosses like Malcolm Wilson.

The World Rally Championship is loaded with incredible incidents, and this DVD features all the Craziest Moments. We're on INSTAGRAM: http://bit.ly/2evtvsg

title: Ural of New England, One of the 50 - The Original Ural Sahara 2WD
description:
www.alphacars.com www.uralne.com 978-263-9000. Each year we look forward to the Ural Factory Engineers and Designers inspiration for the limited edition series. Ural Sahara was one of them and still continues to be by far the most desirable 2WD Ural ever. It is considered to be the Limited Edition for 2008, but it was sold in 2009 as a 2009 Model Year. Unfortunately for all of us there were only 50 Sahara bikes built for the U.S. market and they are pretty much impossible to find, because there owners have absolutely no desire to part with them. 

Also, there were 35 similar specification bikes built for European market as a 2007 Limited Edition. These are even more desirable and are called "Pustinya" (in Russian Desert). In addition to the Sahara specifications these bikes had additional exciting details - Black European Exhaust (pea-shooter), set of German Knobby Tires and a color matched front mounted Ammo Box on the right side of the sidecar. 

Any military theme Ural looks like it just came from the Indiana Jones era, but what makes the "Sahara" and "Pustinya" belong to that era even more is the fact that all bike parts are painted the same color -- bike and sidecar frame, suspensions, arm and levers, wheels ... everything. This is tedious and time consuming process that was only done on "Sahara", "Pustinya" and "Taiga" Limited Edition Urals. On all other Urals these parts are painted in flat black and body parts are painted in specific color.

We at Ural of New England proudly sold 18 out of the 50 Sahara Urals, and due to special circumstances recently got one back in trade. We are very excited and happy to offer this Sahara for your consideration. We took it a step further. Not only we fully reconditioned and thoroughly serviced this bike to meet our high standards, well ... we equipped it with Black European Exhaust (pea-shooter), set of German Knobby Tires and a color matched front mounted Ammo Box on the right side of the sidecar! In addition, we supplied sidecar cover and a spare wheel cover that are made from "Brezent" - material that was used in Russian Military in the old days. This bike has the rugged, elegant and exclusive look and feel! Bike only has 9621km (5979mi) of very well cared operation. After our reconditioning this one-of-fifty Sahara Urals is ready for the showroom floor of any museum or a Cross Country trip through hi-ways, mountains and prairies if needed. it represents museum level quality cosmetic condition as well as top notch mechanical condition that you would expect from Ural of New England team.

title: Ringo Starr - First All Starr Band - Act Naturally
description:
Greek Theatre, September 3rd 1989. 

"Act Naturally" is a song written by Johnny Russell and Voni Morrison, originally recorded by Buck Owens and the Buckaroos, whose version reached number 1 on the Billboard Country Singles chart in 1963, his first chart-topper. In 2002, Shelly Fabian of About.com ranked the song number 169 on her list of the Top 500 Country Music Songs.

Russell, originally from Mississippi, was based in Fresno, California in the early 1960s. One night, some of his friends from Oklahoma planned to do a recording session in Los Angeles and asked him to join them. In order to do so, Russell had to break a date with his then-girlfriend. "When she asked me why I was going to L.A., I answered, 'They are going to put me in the movies and make a big star out of me.' We both laughed."

Thus inspired, Russell quickly came up with a concept for a love song based around his comment. He wrote it that day, and tried to teach it to the singer he was helping in Los Angeles, but he was unable to learn it. Russell then wanted to record it himself, but his then-producer turned it down, claiming that songs about the movies weren't hit material.

A full two years passed before anyone recorded "Act Naturally". "No matter how hard I tried, I couldn't get anyone interested in it," Russell said.

The song has been covered by many other artists, including Loretta Lynn and The Beatles.

The Beatles covered the song in 1965 on their album Help! (in the United Kingdom) and as the B-side of the "Yesterday" single in the U.S..

The Beatles' version is sung by Ringo Starr. Stephen Thomas Erlewine of Allmusic called it "an ideal showcase for Ringo's amiable vocals." They performed the song during an appearance on The Ed Sullivan Show, which was taped on August 14, 1965 and broadcast on September 12, 1965. It was also performed at The Beatles' famous Shea Stadium concert on August 15, 1965 and played at some concerts throughout The Beatles' 1965 U.S. tour (alternating with Ringo's other "hit" song, "I Wanna Be Your Man").

The Beatles recorded the song on June 17, 1965 in 13 takes. The first 12 takes were evidently used to work out the arrangement; the master was take 13, the only take with vocals. It was mixed the following day. The Beatles almost recorded a song by their engineer Norman Smith, but realized that Starr didn't yet have a vocal on Help!. They originally recorded the song "If You've Got Trouble" as Starr's intended song for the album, but were dissatisfied with the results and recorded "Act Naturally" to replace it. It was the last cover they recorded until the Get Back/Let It Be sessions in 1969.

Because Capitol Records' version of the Help! album included only the songs that appeared in the movie, plus incidental music from the film, the label held back "Yesterday" and "Act Naturally" and issued them initially as a non-LP single. As the B-side of the U.S. single, "Act Naturally" peaked at #47 in October 1965. The two songs made their first American album appearance on Yesterday and Today, released in the U.S. on June 20, 1966.

When the single was reissued on Apple Records in 1971, "Act Naturally" had the "full apple" side and "Yesterday" ended up on the "sliced apple" side. That is because "Act Naturally" was the intended A-side and has always been listed as such in Capitol's files.

The song features Ringo Starr on lead vocal, drums, and percussion, Paul McCartney on harmony vocals and bass guitar, John Lennon on acoustic guitar, and George Harrison on lead guitar, which is double-tracked, creating a chorus-like effect.

description:
Frère Jacques (conocida comúnmente en español como Martinillo o Fray Santiago) es una de las canciones populares infantiles más conocidas. De origen francés, puede ser cantada como una melodía simple o como un canon a cuatro voces.
Letra
El original francés, aunque con ligeras variantes, dice:

Frère Jacques, Frère Jacques,
Dormez-vous? Dormez-vous?
Sonnez les matines! Sonnez les matines!
Din, dan, don. Din, dan, don

La traducción literal es:

Hermano Jaime, Hermano Jaime,
¿Duerme usted? ¿Duerme usted?
¡Tocan a maitines! ¡Tocan a maitines!
Din, dan, don. Din, dan, don.

title: NS Online Service Heroes
description:
NS is sinds de eerste tweet door oud-Minister Camiel Eurlings en President-Directeur Bert Meerstadt op 29 maart 2010 actief op Twitter. Inmiddels zijn we bijna 100.000 tweets en 73.000 followers verder. Naast vragen over de dienstverlening en reisinformatie, gaan de online conversaties over producten en winkels op het station en de gratis WiFi-voorziening in de trein. Ook vragen de volgers hulp bij het terug vinden van verloren of vergeten goederen in de trein.

Gerjan Vasse, NS Social Media Manager: "In 2010 is het NS_online twitteraccount geactiveerd om dagelijks online het gesprek met onze reizigers aan te gaan, want alleen samen met de klant kunnen we de dienstverlening beter maken. Dankzij de feedback van onze reizigers hebben we al vele trajecten kunnen verstevigen, defecten aan het station/trein kunnen verhelpen en zijn we in contact gekomen met vele boeiende partijen. Dagelijks helpen we onze klanten in minder dan 140 tekens op weg".

NS_online wordt door een zeer breed publiek gevolgd, van dagjesmensen tot zeer frequente reizigers, journalisten en politici. Iets meer dan de helft van de followers is man (57%) en 76% van de volgers is tussen de 21-45 jaar. De followers zoeken het meest vaak contact tussen 8-10 uur en tussen 15-18 uur. 

Het NS Social media team bestaat sinds 2013 uit een team van meer dan 20 enthousiaste medewerkers, die dagelijks tussen 07- 20u uur en op zaterdag van 09-17u meer dan 200 tweets. Buiten de Online service hours worden grotere verstoringen gemeld via NS_online

NS is niet alleen met NS_online actief op Twitter, andere accounts zijn @NS_Hispeed, @WerkenbijNS en @NS_stations. En natuurlijk ook op Facebook.com/NederlandseSpoorwegen

title: Old & New Dreams band - Lecture-demonstration, part 2
description: In February 1980, the Old and New Dreams band (Don Cherry, Dewey Redman, Charlie Haden and Ed Blackwell) give a concert in Cambridge, MA. As part of the event, on February 29, 1980, Cherry, Redman and Haden presented a lecture-demonstration at Harvard University, focusing on their approach to music and the influence of their mentor Ornette Coleman. I've recently found the recording of that event (made on a low-fi boombox mic) and will upload all I've got, including discussion, audience questions, and musical performances. Enjoy!

The video concludes with a photo run at Ithaca before the train passes under Hwy 127 on the way back to Owosso.

一説には水槽立ち上げ時後、半年くらいは水換え不要だとか、

恐ろしくなりそのままでいました。

小型水槽で換水量も少ないため思ったより

2週間後の現在も元気でいるので

title: Ahora o Nunca: Tráiler En Español HD 1080P
description:
Dirección: Rob Reiner.
País: USA.
Año: 2007.
Duración: 97 min.
Género: Comedia dramática.
Interpretación: Jack Nicholson (Edward Cole), Morgan Freeman (Carter Chambers), Sean Hayes (Thomas), Rob Morrow (Dr. Hollins), Beverly Todd (Virginia), Alfonso Freeman (Roger Chambers), Rowena King (Angelica).
Guión: Justin Zackham.
Producción: Craig Zadan, Neil Meron, Alan Greisman y Rob Reiner.
Música: Marc Shaiman.
Fotografía: John Schwartzman.
Montaje: Robert Leighton.
Diseño de producción: Bill Brzeski.
Vestuario: Molly Maginnis.
Estreno en USA: 11 Enero 2008.
Estreno en España: 1 Febrero 2008.
SINOPSIS

Hace mucho tiempo, el profesor de filosofía de Carter Chambers, en su primer año de carrera, les sugirió a sus estudiantes que elaborasen una "lista de deseos", un recuento de todas las cosas que querían hacer, ver y experimentar en la vida antes de morir. Pero, mientras Carter estaba aún tratando de aclarar sus sueños y planes privados, la realidad se entrometió: matrimonio, hijos, una multitud de responsabilidades y, finalmente, un trabajo de mecánico de automóviles durante 46 años, gradualmente cambiaron su idea de lo que era una lista de deseos en poco más que un recuerdo agridulce de oportunidades perdidas y en un ejercicio mental en el que pensaba de vez en cuando para pasar el tiempo mientras trabajaba bajo la capota de un coche. Entretanto, el multimillonario empresario Edward Cole nunca vio una lista sin pensar en los beneficios. Siempre estaba demasiado atareado haciendo dinero y construyendo un imperio para pensar en cuáles podrían ser sus necesidades más profundas, más allá de la siguiente adquisición o una taza de café para gourmets. Pero entonces la vida les dio a ambos un toque de atención urgente e inesperado. Carter y Edward se encontraron compartiendo una habitación de hospital con mucho tiempo para pensar en lo que sucedería a continuación, y en cuánto de ello estaba en sus manos. A pesar de sus diferencias, pronto descubrieron que tenían dos cosas muy importantes en común: una necesidad no satisfecha de aceptarse a sí mismos y las elecciones que habían hecho, y un deseo urgente de pasar el tiempo que habían perdido haciendo todo lo que siempre quisieron hacer. Así que, en contra de las órdenes del médico y del sentido común, estos dos auténticos desconocidos abandonan el hospital y se lanzan juntos a la carretera para vivir la aventura de sus vidas.

title: ¿Cómo preparar Ravioles de Espinaca y Queso? - Cocina Fresca
tags: ['tips', 'cocina', 'sabores', 'walmart', 'cocinar', 'preparar', 'ingredientes', 'frescura', 'siempre fresco', 'precios bajos', 'hoy y siempre', 'carrito', 'gente walmart', 'tienda en linea', 'walmart.com.mx', 'catalogos', 'folletos', 'tiendas', 'ofertas', 'buen fin', '@walmart', 'Walmart mexico', 'martes de frescura', 'ravioles', 'queso', 'espinaca', 'ravioles de espinaca y queso', 'ravioles de queso', 'ravioles de espinaca', 'en 20', 'ravioles de queso con espinaca', 'navidad', 'cena', 'cena navideña']
description:
Suscríbete aquí http://bit.ly/CFYTSUB

Para 3 a 4 porciones:

Para la pasta:
  Harina de trigo 1/2 kg
  Yema de huevo 4 pzas
  Sal 1 cdita
  Aceite vegetal 1 cda
  Agua 1/4 taza

Para el relleno:
  Queso doble crema 250g      
         Espinaca baby 4 tazas 
         Sal 1 cdita 
  Pimienta 1 cdita 

Para el relleno:
 1. Corta la espinaca 
 2. Desmorona el queso con la ayuda de un tenedor 
 3. En un recipiente, mezcla la espinaca con el queso
 4. Agrega la sal y la pimienta
 mezcla bien 

Procedimiento para la pasta
 1. En un recipiente,agrega la harina
 2. Forma un orificio en el centro y vacía las yemas, el aceite y el agua 
 3. Amasa hasta formar una pasta pegajosa
 4. Sigue amasando por 10 minutos hasta obtener una consistencia suave
Sobre una superficie plana amasa por otros 5 minutos 
Corta la masa por la mitad
 5. Con la ayuda de un rodillo extiende la pasta 
 6. Deja 1/2 cm de grosor y dobla con cuidado
Extiende la otra mitad al mismo grosor, intentando que quede del mismo tamaño que la anterior 
 7. Con un cuchillo marca una cuadrícula de 5x5 cm sin cortar la pasta 
 8. Con una cuchara, toma una medida del relleno
 9. Coloca el relleno en el centro de cada cuadrícula
 10. Con un poco de agua, moja tus dedos 
 11. Moja ligeramente las orillas de cada cuadro 
 12. Coloca  la otra pasta encima 
Presiona por todas las orillas de cada cuadro
Corta los bordes 
 13. Corta cuadros para formar los ravioles 
 14. Con un tenedor presiona las orillas para que cierren bien 
 15. En una olla con agua hirviendo, agrega una cucharada de sal.
Coloca los ravioles y deja cocer por 5 minutos 
 16. Retira del agua y escurre en papel absorbente

Todo lo necesario para hacer esta receta lo puedes encontrar en Walmart

title: How to reset the service light on the Volvo 850, 1993, 1994 and 1995 year models. - Auto Care Series
description:
This video will show you how to reset the SERVICE light in the 1993, 1994, and 1995 Volvo 850 cars. A7-4-1-5-1

These cars have an OBD-1 diagnosis tool under the hood near the ECU box. The light comes on every 5,000 miles to remind you to have the oil changed.

*** This procedure only works with the VDO cluster. If you have the Yazaki cluster (tach goes to 8000 rpms) you will need to pull the faceplate plug and poke something through there to reset the reminder.

The 1996 - 1998 Volvo 850's and S/V70's have a maintenance light system that requires a special OBD-II scanner to reset the light, found at the dealer and/or a specialty independent Volvo repair shop. One can be found online for purchase for $70+ US dollars. Most people simply take the bulb out, it's only an oil change reminder.

description:
Would you like your choir to perform a Karl Jenkins piece especially written for you?

'Motets' is a brand new album of a cappella choral works by Karl Jenkins, and Boosey & Hawkes and DCINY are running a very special competition in honour of its release.

Simply video your choir performing any track from 'Motets', upload the video to YouTube, tweet or post online using the hashtag #SingMotets and email us a link to your video to choraluk@boosey.com

The prize will be a brand new short a cappella choral work composed by Karl Jenkins for the lucky winning choir, and dedicated to them! The winning choir will also have the exclusive opportunity to present the world premiere performance of the piece.

Here at DCINY we were so excited about the competition that we wanted to do something to get the ball rolling. So here's our rendition of 'Laudamus Te' -- enjoy!

title: Minecraft Castle Defense System
description:
Update: You can find an updated video here: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OAnZ_HLocnU

First of all: sorry for the weird colors and the weird watermark... My screen-recording program is kinda weird =S. Anyway;
This is a security system I built into my castle (it's all explained in the video, be sure to turn annotations on). If you remove a block, lava will come falling down and the ground will disappear from under you. This is all achieved with torches and gravity (gravel). I also show a small part of my city. The only things I cheated are armor and tools... All the materials were gathered.

The closing gate works as follows:
There's a tower of gravel with a torch attached. On the torch is another pile of gravel, on which there is another torch etc.
If the first tower of gravel starts to move because of gravity (i.e. removing one block) the torch disappears, which makes the gravel fall and the other torches disappear. The gate is closed with gravel.

The falling lava works like this:
It's actually pretty easy and works with the same system as the gate. Some torches are attached to the gravel that's supposed to close the gate when the system is used. On top of those torches is a block of gravel, and on top of that is some lava. When the torches are destroyed because of the falling gravel, the gravel that traps the lava falls down one block and releases the lava. It then comes down through the shaft to drop onto the bridge.

The disappearing ground works like this:
This one is a bit more complicated. You can't actually see anything of this happening, except for the disappearing ground itself. When the triggerblock is destroyed, a torch inside the wall gets destroyed. On the torch there is a block of gravel and on that there is a spring block of water. When the torch is destroyed, the gravel falls down and the water is released into a small series of tubes. There are some torches in the tube system and when the water hits them, they are destroyed. On top of the torches is once again some gravel, which is trapping more water, but one block higher than the water that's already there. The released water then flows under the gate to destroy some torches holding up the gravel and the gravel falls into a hole all the way to the bottom of the map (I'm not kidding... You can even fall out of the map if you remove a block at the bottom).

I hope this explained =P. Enjoy!
(Oh, and also I show a small part of my city by looking around...)

EDIT: I've updated part of the trap. All three blocks of the ground now fall at the same time, instead of two first and then another one.

description:
Der Hotelmodus von Mord in Greenrock Village ist ein Brettspiel für 2-4 Spieler. Dabei müssen die im Hotel verübten Morde aufgeklärt werden. Gleichzeitig entwickeln sich 15 spannende Detektivgeschichten. Wer sammelt die meisten Beweise und erhält dadurch die meisten Punkte?

Die neue Mörder- und Kriminalspiel-Reihe von JUMBO dreht sich rund um die seltsamen Morde im kleinen verschlafenen Ort Greenrock Village. Mit einem Solitärspiel für eine Person und einem großen Brettspiel kommen gleich zwei neue Spiele in diesem Jahr auf den Markt. Helf sie mit die Mörder in Greenrock Village zu finden.

Nora, die Managerin der Rockgruppe "Die Heulende Wölfe" ist ermordet worden. Ihr markerschütternder Schrei war durch das ganze Hotel zu hören. Und das soll etwas heißen, bei der lautstarken Musik ihrer Rockgruppe. Die Polizei tappt bei der Tätersuche völlig im Dunkeln. Wer kann Noras Mörder hinter Gitter bringen?

description:
Full Playlist: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLLALQuK1NDrhWzO_Voh44foRbw1Ei7Ce5
-
-
Like these MMA lessons !!! Check out the official app http://apple.co/1DIxHwS

Watch more How to Do MMA Submission Holds videos: http://www.howcast.com/videos/514141-How-to-Do-an-Arm-In-Guillotine-Choke-MMA-Submissions



All right guys, now we're going to do a traditional arm in guillotine and the history of the guillotine is very interesting. It was invented by Renzo Gracie, and so he has some great tricks to finish. I'm going to show a great arm in guillotine, his style, and then also my backup plan off that guillotine.  Because remember, Jujitsu is all about position and plan B.  Come up, sit back, get the grip, arm in, fall to the side.  Again.  One, I come up, I reach around his head and I snake around and make a fist.  Grab my fist.  I fall this way.  

I cross my feet, this foot on top. Now, I turn my head to touch my own knee as I pull upwards.  Two important points. One, fall to the side.  Second, pull upwards, not this.  This.  We call this Yo-Ho-Ho, like you're a pirate.  This, this.  That is essential to the move. One more time.  One, sit back, reach around, get your grip, fall to the side, cross your feet.  Now, I have the tap, but let's say I don't.  I take my foot, put it in here, flip him over, and I can come to the mount, finish him here.  If I can't get to the mount, I come to my knees, and I can finish him here.  We'll go over this submission later. One more time.  That's the arm in guillotine.

title: HALO World Premiere - End of set 2 - June 5th, 2009 - Lake Helen, FL
description:
I played the Pantheon Steel HALO for the first time anywhere in public on June 5th, 2009. IT was a small gathering at the Lake Helen Coffee and Tea Company, in Lake Helen Florida. This was one of the last songs of the evening. The show was billed as "Ruminations 2 - Improvisations on Panart Hang and Pantheon Steel HALO". 

Honestly, I only played the Hang for one song. The HALO has many characteristics that make it quite enjoyable to play. I've already noticed a change in my style of play between the HALO and the Hang. The HALO seems to draw a different energy from me. It is an instrument within itself. Some people find an inherent "magic" within the Hang, and think perhaps that unique quality is otherwise un-acheivable. After playing my HALO, I can't describe the feelings I've had in any other way. A deep, penetrating magic, that reverberates within me both figuratively and literally. You "feel" the music, both within your body, and within your soul. But I suppose magic is within the soul of the beholder. It may not affect others as the Hang. But I know what it does for me. And I can tell you, playing the HALO is a wonderful experience. It will be fun to explore the sonic possibilities with the HALO. 

You can find more information about the HALO at http://halo.pantheonsteel.com

title: 1999 Iowa @ Illinois - Tirapelle vs. Williams (Part 2)
description:
Feb 14th, 1999 - Iowa visits Champaign, Illinois and a packed Huff Hall in what proves to be a showdown for the ages.  Illinois leads the dual 17-13 with two matches remaining at 149lbs and 157lbs.  At 149lbs, #1 ranked and unbeaten TJ Williams (Iowa) takes on #9 ranked Adam Tirapelle (Illinois) with the dual on the line in a match that is literally decided in the final second.

Illinois goes on to win the dual with an upset victory by Griff Powell (Illinois) over #5 Jaime Heidt (Iowa) at 157lbs to give Illinois their first victory over the Iowa Hawkeyes in 47 years!

description:
READ!!

2345 Jahre später ... kam ein neues Video XD
Jaa ich weiß, es ist nicht der Burner .__. hoffe es gefällt euch trotzdem.
Wollte mal zeigen, dass ich nicht ganz so inaktiv bin.

Story:
Der Junge hat seine große Liebe verloren und trauert um sie. Sie erscheint als Engel um an seiner Seite zu sein, im Kraft zu geben (Sie kann sich auch nicht im Tode von ihm trennen, weil sie ihn liebt). 
Eines Tages sieht sie ihn mit einem neuen Mädchen. Sie beobachtet die beiden wochenlang aus dem Hintergrund und als sie das Bild auf der Kommode entdeckt wird ihr klar, wie ernst es ihrem Freund mit dem neuen Mädchen ist.
Sie sucht die beiden und erkennt dann doch, dass sie los lassen muss, dass ihr Freund es verdient hat wieder glücklich zu sein und geliebt zu werden.
ENDE XD

~
The Story is about a boy, which had lost his true love. She appeared as an angel, to be by his side and give him strength. ( She couldn't leave him even in the dead)
One day she saw her boyfriend with a new girl. She observed them for weeks and as she saw the picture on his commode, she realized, how serious he meaned it to the new girl.
She searched for them and as she saw them, she realized, that she had to let him go and he deserves to be happy again and to be loved.

Rate, commentate, subscribe ...blablabla xD
Kritik erwünscht, aber konstruktiv! Ich weiß, es is nicht mein bestes Video °^°
DANKEE an Holy und OneChanPictures

title: :: Freshlook Colorblends Gray :: Review!
description:
Hi guys. Here is a review of the Freshlook Colorblends Toric Gray contacts. I know a lot of you go to youtube to find your information so I'm doing what little I can to help you all. I got these from Wal-Mart. I ordered in the morning and got them the next day, they are delivered by 1800contacts.com

To begin, I wear toric contact lenses. Toric lenses correct astigmatism, and because of this there is a major price difference. $37 for regular contacts, $69.99 for a toric prescription. If you have astigmatism but you just want to change your eye color, you can go ahead and wear any colored lens. Circle lens, Freshlook, Acuvue2 whatever, as long as you have a +0 power on the lens (no prescription. You can ONLY wear toric lenses if you want vision correction properties while having astigmatism!)

I wore these lenses for 12 hours yesterday between 11:30am and 11:30pm with no true irritation. My eyes had redness, but It's not like my eyes were killing me, I didn't even know my eyes were red because they felt fine. At 5pm when I got home I put used a redness relief formula eye drops. I got it from Dollar Tree for $1 of course. I wear lenses aggressively because I lost my eyeglasses. I wore these all day with no problems. Having eye drops is a basic responsibility you have if you wear contacts for long periods of time.

title: Dirt3 - Citroën C4 WRX - Michigan
description:
Bien, aquí otra muestra de este espectacular juego de simulación. A decir verdad hay algunas cosas que no me gustan pero en un análisis mas general creo que puede mantenerme ocupado durante un buen tiempo. Si bien los rallies son mis favoritos, y en este los hay, creo que podrían haber incorporado tramos más largos, aunque sea en instancias finales o avanzadas. Aunque hay que ser MUY preciso para poder lograr puestos decorosos jugando en nivel avanzado, al ser tramos cortos uno termina agarrandole la mano bastante rápido ya que dentro de un trazado siempre son unas pocas curvas las que nos hacen perder segundos. En el modo traiblazer la sensación de velocidad está más acorde que en el resto del juego, que, a mi parecer es un poquitin exagerada. Los duelos mano a mano son interesantes pero la IA es bastante benévola. El Rally-Cross es Dirt2 con lavado de cara y mejor física, interesante para amenizar los tramos en solitario del rally (como dijo mi amigo marrano), pero al igual que los mano a mano la IA no la pone muy dificil. El GimKhANA...bue´h solo a los yankies se les ocurrió meterlo a Ken Block a correr rallies (que no ensarta una curva)  y también a ellos se les ocurrió mezclar rally con gimkhana. Novedoso y entretenido los dos primeros desafíos, después un bodrio. A los que les gusta, lo van a disfrutar mucho ya que está bien logrado. Particularmente no lo hubiera agregado al igual que las carreritas de buggies y trucks. Bueno éstas son mis impresiones en lo que hace al juego en general. Con respecto al apartado técnico está 9 puntos: mejoras gráficas (no son para decir WOW!!), mejoras en las físicas (ídem al anterior), muy bien aprovechado el procesamiento gráfico (en mi caso va mejor que con Dirt2 y todo full con 8xQMSSA). Bugs, hasta ahora solo el del volante que no guarda la configuración en el perfil y hay que cargarlo cada vez que se inicia el jugo.

En este video era la primera vez que corría este tramo, en dificultad Avanzado+, sin ABS y editado para evitar las cámaras tipo de seguimiento que son muy poco reales y para poder escuchar al navegante. Sin mapa, solo siguiendo las notas. La verdad que ha quedado bastante real a la hora de verlo completo.
Espero que lo disfruten.
Saludos.

title: CYBERPOWERPC FANGBOOK EVO Product Tour
description:
An absurd amount of high performance hardware can be packed in our FANGBOOK EVO notebooks. Normally, cramming all of these components into a notebook results in an insanely heavy, ugly-looking monstrosity. FANGBOOK EVO has been cleverly engineered to avoid excess bulk and maintain the aesthetic one would expect from a gaming notebook. Measuring just 16.85" (L) x 11.34" (W) x 2.17" and weighing under 8 pounds with the high-capacity 9-cell Lithium Ion battery installed, carrying around the FANGBOOK EVO won't remind you of your high school textbook-lugging days.

Roommates, spouses, teachers, and neighbors aren't always going to be on board with your gaming desires. Thanks to the full-size 102 key red LED-backlit gaming keyboard on the FANGBOOK EVO, you can keep on chugging well after lights out or quiet hours. Darkness isn't an issue for the FANGBOOK EVO - never miss a keystroke thanks to the adjustable keyboard backlighting. The keyboard's layout is also gamer-friendly; the Windows key has been relocated to the right side of the spacebar to avoid those accidental presses that minimize your game - an ideal configuration for WASD gamers. Anti-ghosting technology also allows the simultaneous pressing of multiple keys and ensures that each key registers correctly.

Just because the FANGBOOK EVO is a notebook doesn't mean it's lacking in input and output ports. The left side of the notebook features two USB 2.0 ports along with the slim optical drive. On the right side you'll find three USB 3.0 ports, an SD (XC/HC) card reader, and 4 audio ports including headphone out, microphone in, line in and line out. In addition to the DC power input, the back of the notebook also sports the VGA, HDMI, and Mini DisplayPort outputs. A Kensington Security Slot on the back of the machine also allows you lock your FANGBOOK EVO down while you're away or in a public place.

Learn more at http://www.cyberpowerpc.com/LandingPages/FangbookEVO/?utm_source=youtube

Ich habe ihn auf der Suche nach einem Opel Diplomat bei einem älteren Herrn entdeckt. Er hatte den Wagen 1979 in einem Autohaus in Wiesbaden gekauft um ihn als Firmenfahrzeug zu nutzen. Auf Grund einer plötzlichen schweren Erkrankung des Besitzers wurde der Wagen aber nie in Betrieb genommen und auch nicht angemeldet und stand 34 Jahre in einer dunkeln trockenen Garage. Der Caprice hat wirklich erst 40 Km auf dem Tacho! Der Wagen wurde damals und später immer mal wieder mit einem leichten Ölfilm Konserviert! Ich habe ihn in diesem Zustand belassen und nichts daran verändert.Deshalb die verstaubte Optik! Unter dieser Schicht wirklich makelloser Lack und Chrom! Im jungfräulichen Innenraum riecht es noch nach Neuwagen. Gummis und Schläuche sind auch Top! Absoluter Auslieferungszustand! An dem Wagen wurde absolut nichts verändert!!! Es sind alle Papiere wie Quittung,deutscher Blanko Brief,Scheckheft,Zollpapiere usw.vorhanden. Der Motor läuft einwandfrei und die Bremsen sind frei. Er ist fahrbereit und hat alle möglichen Extras wie elekrische Sitzbank,Scheibenantenne,Klima,Color usw. Da er mir zu schade ist ihn selbst zu fahren und ich kein Sammler bin möchte ich ihn gerne verkaufen. Falls Interesse besteht können sie den Wagen gerne in Wiesbaden besichtigen.

yes the pages are numbered one off. yes i know i didn't play it exactly as it was written since i just wanted to play it easily at the time, because i wanted it recorded asap.


This is me playing Heaven by DJ Sammy on the piano (yes I know DJ Sammy didn't make the song, but im playing his version of it).

Its not perfect, but it was close enough haha.

Im wearing the headphones because I had my computer hooked up beside the piano with the headset as well as the video camera picking up sound. At the begining I looked up at the computer monitor to make sure everything was recording ok.

And yes, I know it is a bit fast.

title: 38 Dan Leckie Way #3107 | Virtual Tour | TheRealtorGroup.ca
description:
This fabulous one-year-new luxury high-rise has set the standards for extravagance and elegance amongst Cityplace projects. Considered by residents as "Concorde's best project to date", the distinct tower is aesthetically dynamic, functionally responsive and structurally efficient. The unique egg-shaped floor plan of the structure creates a building curvature that captures panoramic views of the city, lake and beyond. Featuring ultra trendy Italian finishes throughout, stainless steel appliances and a very spacious/practical one-plus-den floor plan, dowtown living really doesn't get any better than this!

The experience begins from the moment you walk into the suite and notice the soaring nine-foot ceilings. As you make your way within, the rich mahogany wood flooring radiates and immediately dominates your attention. That is, until you come across the hi-tech Euro-style kitchen, which is ultra-contemporary and comes fully equipped with a modern six-foot cylindrical hood fan, cooking island with roll-out table, full-height pantry units for extra storage, drawers with soft closure, plus much more. The chic four-piece bath features a glass rain-shower stall and rectangular drop-in sink. Floor-to-ceiling windows allow for panoramic views, a large master that maximizes space and a very functional den that can be used as another room make this unit stand out amongst the rest: a definite must-see.

As a Cityplace resident of Panorama, you'll have the opportunity to enjoy Canada's largest and most renowned facility centre, featuring over eight acres of world class amenities including: a twenty-four hour concierge service, fitness centre, sports lounge, internet café, rooftop patio with Afresco bar, mini theatre, sauna, party room and the list goes on.

title: Let's Play: Doom 2 (Map26) - The Abandoned Mines
description:
A playthrough of "The Abandoned Mines" (Map26) of Doom II: Hell on Earth for PC, played through GLBoom. 100% kills, 100% secrets (Max-Kill).

You are not safe anywhere in this map. Seriously. Every place in this map is connected to itself in some fashion it seems, and usually via open windows or tiny alcoves where Chaingunners can snipe from. It's small and deadly. You have to constantly be on your toes and aware of your surroundings, and a little bit of knowledge of where enemies and items are in this map is a huge help on top of that. Enemy placement is painful, but it isn't annoying. As long as you keep your cool and know what's ahead or know what's around you, this isn't as hard as it seems.

Definitely a nicely designed, wonderful looking map. Sadly underrated though.

description:

les subo un video del untimo trabajo realizado aunque le falta...
Puedes hacer un bonsai casi de cualquier árbol. Hay seis especies de olivos que han sido transformadas en bonsai. Las especies negra, verde y salvaje son todas susceptibles de transformarse en árboles en miniatura. Disfrutan mucho del sol, pero no pueden tolerar la helada. Puedes crear un bonsai de olivo desde la semilla o desde un esqueje. Comenzar con el esqueje es la forma más rápida de crear un olivo en miniatura.

title: Trenes en la Nieve-Producciones Vicari.(Juan Franco Lazzarini)
tags: ['PRODUCCIONES', 'VICARI.', 'Juan', 'Franco', 'Lazzarini', 'Train (Transit Vehicle Type)', 'Las lluvias', 'nevadas intensas', 'peligrosas', 'rescate', 'grave desastre', 'acumulación de nieve', 'son tempestades', 'congelación', 'Snow (Literature Subject)', 'vientos fuertes', 'Entrañan un peligro', 'personas', 'para el ganado.', 'siembran el caos', 'carreteras y ferrocarriles']
description:
Las lluvias y nevadas intensas son
peligrosas para las comunidades vulnerables. Pueden
dificultar las actividades de rescate y rehabilitación a raíz
de un grave desastre, como ocurrió con el terremoto de
Pakistán, en octubre de 2005. Pueden sumir en el caos el
transporte por carretera y por ferrocarril, y la infraestructura
y redes de comunicación. La acumulación de nieve puede
causar el hundimiento de los tejados de los edificios.
Los vientos fuertes entrañan un peligro para la aviación, para
los marineros y pescadores, así como para estructuras muy
elevadas como torres, mástiles y grúas
Las ventiscas son tempestades violentas que se
desencadenan con temperaturas por debajo del punto de
congelación y con vientos fuertes y ventiscas de nieve.
Entrañan un peligro para las personas y para el ganado.
Provocan el cierre de los aeropuertos, y siembran el caos en
carreteras y ferrocarriles

title: 2005 BMW 645Ci Convertible
description:
http://www.autosofpalmbeach.com/cgi-bin/showroom.cgi?d_id=1078
Have you ever wondered what it would be like to drive the embodiment of an emotion? Perhaps that emotion is joy. What would it be like to drive something that brings sheer joy to its driver? Now you can know exactly what that feels like with your new Silver Gray Metallic 2005 BMW 645Ci Convertible with Navigation, Sport Package, Premium Sound Package, and Satellite Radio is one of the most stunning cars on the road. The 645Ci is a beautiful car that will draw many stares wherever you go. Not only does it look great, but it has also been treated well with an unbelievably low 31,830 miles on it. From its great sport package with stylish wheels to its premium sound package for an optimum listening experience, this car has everything you'll need for a beautiful, luxurious, and classy convertible that can be driven all year. Let's see what this awesome car has to offer you.

EXTERIOR: The body of your new 645Ci looks great covered in a luscious coat of SILVER GRAY METALLIC paint. The color is absolutely beautiful and the perfect color to complement the outstanding design. The paint is in great shape with no scrapes, scratches or serious blemishes to mention. After all, it still has less than 32,000 miles on it. This great car has a fantastic engine to go with its great looks: a six speed automatic 4.4L DOHC V8 engine with 325 horsepower and 330 lb-ft of torque. This means that the car doesn't hesitate when your foot hits the gas pedal! The car's sport package (that retailed new at around $2,800) adds great wheels and tires and unique features on the inside! You'll love the way the car feels as you drive. The black soft top is in great shape with no rips or tears. It works perfectly and goes up and down with just an easy push of a button. Xenon adaptive automatic headlights outfit the front of the car for outstanding visibility in all driving situations. Rain-sensing windshield wipers are another great addition because they will turn on automatically when the heavens let loose. The power heated auto-dimming mirrors tilt down as you reverse so that you can see the ground as you back up. This is undoubtedly a beautiful car.

INTERIOR: The interior is outfitted in very plush CREAM BEIGE upholstery complemented by wood trim. It's very likely your friends have never seen such a nice color combination before! The car smells clean and fresh with no foul odors, whether from smoke or anything else. The 8-way power front sport bucket seats feel comfortable and thanks to the sport package they also have thigh and lateral support! To help keep you comfortable there is dual-zone automatic climate control with auto air circulation and other great functions. One of the nicest features of the vehicle is the iDrive system with BMW navigation system. For navigation, you'll have turn by turn directions and maps so you can always get to your destinations easily and you'll know exactly where you are. Also housed in the same unit are on-screen visual controls for the climate, car options, and entertainment. The upgraded AM/FM stereo with CD player sounds absolutely superb for top-notch listening. There's even Sirius so you can get all the great channels that satellite radio has to offer. With the parking sensors you will get visual and audio alerts as you park so that you wont hit objects as you park. Some other great features are: tire pressure monitor, power windows and locks, wireless communication, alarm system, cruise control, courtesy lights, locking glovebox, auxiliary audio input, and cupholders. Further, your new car comes with mats, books, and one key with built-in remote.

Our goal is to make sure the overall condition of the car is as close to new as possible. This means a full detail that includes polishing any light scratches and professionally touching up chips. All dings are professionally removed. While our cars are close-to-new, keep in mind that they are pre-owned and may show some signs of wear. We will be more than happy to go over the car panel-by-panel with you on the phone for extra details. Also, think of the great savings you will have with this purchase. The MSRP for this car new was $82,790 with all the great options! You can avoid paying too much money while still driving an awesome car. Prepare to put the top down and enjoy driving joy. And by joy we mean your new 2005 BMW 645Ci Convertible!
